{"title_page": "1877\u201378 Dumbarton F.C. season", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2015}}\n{{Infobox football club season\n| club        = [[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n| season      = 1877\u201378\n| manager     = \n| chairman    = \n| stadium     = Townend, Dumbarton\n| cup1        = [[1877\u201378 Scottish Cup|Scottish Cup]]\n| cup1 result = Second Round\n\n| league topscorer   = \n| season topscorer   = \n| highest attendance = \n| lowest attendance  = \n| average attendance = \n\n| pattern_la1 = \n| pattern_b1  = \n| pattern_ra1 = \n| pattern_sh1 = _navy_sides\n| pattern_so1 = \n| leftarm1    = 1d1f4d\n| body1       = 1d1f4d\n| rightarm1   = 1d1f4d\n| shorts1     = ffffff\n| socks1      = ff0000\n| prevseason  = [[1876\u201377 Dumbarton F.C. season|1876\u201377]]\n| nextseason  = [[1878\u201379 Dumbarton F.C. season|1878\u201379]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1877\u201378''' season was the fifth [[Football in Scotland|Scottish football]] season in which [[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]] competed at a national level.\n\n==Scottish Cup==\n{{Main|1877\u201378 Scottish Cup}}\n\nDuring the early years of the [[Scottish Cup]], the earlier rounds of the competition were played on a regional basis, which was always a tough proposition as three of the top Scottish clubs at the time were from Dumbartonshire.  This season Dumbarton came up against Vale of Leven in the second round, and lost (to the eventual champions) after a 1-1 draw.<ref>{{cite book | last = Smailes | first = Gordon | title = The Breedon Book of Scottish Football Records | publisher = Breedon Books | year = 1995 | location = Derby | isbn = 1-85983-020-X}}</ref>\n\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  =W\n|date =29 September 1877\n|round = [[1877\u201378 Scottish Cup#First Round|Cup R1]]\n|score = 4-0<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fitbastats.com/dumbarton/game.php?gameid=38125 |title=Dumbarton 4 - 1 Waverley, Scottish Cup (29/09/1877) |publisher=Fitbastats.com |accessdate=7 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sonsarchive.com/matchdetails.php?id=20 |title=Dumbarton 4-0 Waverley, Saturday, September 29th, 1877 |publisher=The Sons Archive |accessdate=7 June 2019}}</ref>\n|team1 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|team2 =Waverley\n|goals1 =Lawrence {{goal|}}{{goal|}}<br>McMaster {{goal|}}<br>Anderson {{goal|}}\n|goals2 = \n|stadium =[[Dumbarton]]\n|attendance =\n|referee =\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  =D\n|date =20 October 1877\n|round = [[1877\u201378 Scottish Cup#Second Round|Cup R2]]\n|score = 1-1<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sonsarchive.com/matchdetails.php?id=21 |title=Dumbarton 1-1 Vale of Leven, Saturday, October 20th, 1877 |publisher=The Sons Archive |accessdate=7 June 2019}}</ref>\n|team1 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|team2 =[[Vale of Leven F.C.|Vale of Leven]]\n|goals1 = {{goal|}}\n|goals2 = {{goal|}}\n|stadium =[[Dumbarton]]\n|attendance =3,000\n|referee =\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  =L\n|date =27 October 1877\n|round = [[1877\u201378 Scottish Cup#Second Round replay|Cup R2r]]\n|score = 4-1<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sonsarchive.com/matchdetails.php?id=22 |title=Vale of Leven 4-1 Dumbarton, Saturday, October 27th, 1877 |publisher=The Sons Archive |accessdate=7 June 2019}}</ref>\n|team1 =[[Vale of Leven F.C.|Vale of Leven]]\n|team2 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|goals1 =Paton {{goal|}}<br> {{goal|}}<br> {{goal|}}<br> {{goal|}}\n|goals2 =Meikleham {{goal|}}\n|stadium =[[Alexandria, West Dunbartonshire|Alexandria]]\n|attendance =5,000\n|referee =\n|motm =\n}}\n\n==Friendlies==\n\nDuring the season, 12 'friendly' matches were played, including home and away fixtures against local teams Renton and Alexandria, and also Glasgow sides, Rangers and South Western. Of these matches, 8 were won, 1 drawn and 3 lost, scoring 32 goals and conceding 8.\n\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  =W\n|date =1 September 1877\n|round = [[Friendly match|Friendly]]\n|score = 2-1\n|repo